          "<strong>Reconciling a bank statement</strong> means comparing your checkbook register to the bank's record to <strong>balance the account</strong> and find the true balance. If the bank's balance is <strong>higher</strong> than your register, you likely wrote checks after the statement period that haven't cleared yet.",
