    "traps": "<strong>Don't mix net-worth liabilities with monthly expenses</strong> — rent and utilities are NOT liabilities, only outstanding debt (loan balances, credit card balance) counts. <strong>Save vs. invest:</strong> short-term goals = save, long-term goals = invest. <strong>Debit vs. credit:</strong> only credit cards build your credit score; only debit cards eliminate debt risk. <strong>Present vs. future value:</strong> if asked what money is worth later you need the interest rate; the present value is what you already hold. On <strong>credit-card balance math</strong>, apply the finance charge to the PREVIOUS balance before adding new charges. <strong>Earned vs. unearned income:</strong> interest and dividends are unearned; tips and salary are earned. Too much <strong>diversification</strong> hurts (dilutes gains) — it's not always 'more is better.'"
